title.narrative: AVAILABILITY OF QUALITY Early Child Development (ECD) AND FAMILY SERVICES TO CHILDREN

description.narrative: Increased availability of quality Early Child Development (ECD) & Family services to children (0-6 years) and their families, in targeted districts, which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence. title.narrative: Increased availability of quality ECD & Family services to children (0-6 years) and their families, in targeted districts

description.narrative: The number of ECD spaces increased from 4,501 in 2018 to 23,191 in 2021 . This was attributed to the increased uptake of home-based ECD services through the national expanded public works programme. A total of 758,505 children (aged 0-6 years) received integrated ECD services. Of these, 19,753 children (10,384 girls, 9,369 boys) received direct support from UNICEF and its partners. A total of 4,530 caregivers (3,334 women, 1,197 men) were trained to provide quality ECD services. An integrated package of ECD services across nutrition, WASH, social protection, child protection and play-based early learning was implemented in 22 UNICEF-supported districts. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2021
